KALAWA JAZMEE is not going anywhere. It’s the longest running independent black-owned record label that’s been here for more than two decades.

 These were the words of Zynne “Mahoota” Sebika and Oscar “Oskido” Mdlongwa, who both said the record label had been around for 24 years.They poured cold water on rumours that Kalawa’s artists were jumping ship and the empire was crumbling.if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");var viewReq = new Array();function vu(u) {var i=new Image();i.src=u.replace("&amp;","&");viewReq.push(i);}vu("https://securepubads.g.doubleclick.net/pcs/view?xai\x3dAKAOjsuRtQaARUG6isx9OTgBTgHITpXrvP4otAdvUF48dtCTjv9tcHNLTXv04j5u3u5Z-z_Uu3xtwr89jJG5EZJOnw0BNiJPUV7gO9j4OliRbrbfIdRjG6wDWuJ8X1a3iQ-86XToJMd6OcOVvTLGBxKGheLKKW_S5TYJbqG5CZq4iQqT91ClQVYGGISitrDoADdMp0-RnZ7fQsfcCDz6--Seox_AO8lDA8zRScVvjCNsGD2uBO-AA_kbFlmoLzivDu_P6l02vrq_auli2q-_hBbSldbzDQrBZ3o\x26sig\x3dCg0ArKJSzAXZigq3RJruEAE\x26urlfix\x3d1\x26adurl\x3d")

   
